notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T05:38:33.995Z",maintainer-agent,"Design rationale: merge drivers keep every output parseable and preserve commutative context. They report semantic conflicts instead of writing raw markers, and defer non-commutative current-item/history reconciliation to explicit validate plus history-repair governance."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T05:38:33.306Z",maintainer-agent,A deterministic union of divergent history can be hash-chain valid while intentionally diverging from the independently merged current item. Treat strict verification as the post-merge detector and history-repair as the explicit reconciliation step; prove both in real Git acceptance tests.
